Haymarket May Buy Stake in India’s BBC Magazines, Sky Reports

-- B y   Z i j i n g   W u
-- 
2011-05-01T15:41:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-01/haymarket-may-buy-stake-in-india-s-bbc-magazines-sky-reports.html
Haymarket Media Group Ltd. is in talks
to purchase a stake in the Indian editions of the British
Broadcasting Corp.’s magazines, including Top Gear, Sky News
reported.  Haymarket, founded by Lord Heseltine, is one of several
potential buyers, the London-based broadcaster said, citing
unidentified people familiar with the talks. The BBC and
Heseltine declined to comment, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zijing Wu in  London  at   zwu17@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeff St.Onge at   jstonge@bloomberg.net . 